  "solution": {
    "rootCauseOptions": [
      { "id": "rc1", "label": "sbox_mux drives a high-capacitance net into a heavy LUT input (n_mux_y has 85 ps of wire delay and feeds a 0.004 pF pin)", "correct": true },
      { "id": "rc2", "label": "Clock skew between state_reg_7 and state_reg_3", "correct": false },
      { "id": "rc3", "label": "Missing false_path on the state feedback loop", "correct": false },
      { "id": "rc4", "label": "Hold violation disguised as setup", "correct": false }
    ],
    "acceptedFixes": [
      {
        "id": "size_up_mux",
        "description": "Size sbox_mux from MUX4X1 to MUX4X4 to drive n_mux_y faster",
        "category": "size_up",
        "ppaCost": { "area": 0.12, "power": 0.08, "timing": -0.2 },
        "slackDelta": 0.22
      },
      {
        "id": "buffer_insert",
        "description": "Insert a BUFX4 on n_mux_y between sbox_mux and sbox_lut",
        "category": "buffer_insert",
        "ppaCost": { "area": 0.05, "power": 0.04, "timing": -0.12 },
        "slackDelta": 0.15
      },
      {
        "id": "useful_skew",
        "description": "Apply useful skew: delay capture clock on state_reg_3 by 100 ps",
        "category": "useful_skew",
        "ppaCost": { "area": 0.02, "power": 0.01, "timing": -0.05 },
        "slackDelta": 0.10
      }
    ]
  },
  "hintTree": {
    "nudge": "Before changing anything, look at where the delay is accumulating. Which single segment of the data path contributes the most?",
    "hint": "Compare cell delays (arcs) vs net delays. You should see one net with unusually high wire delay — investigate what's driving it and what it's feeding.",
    "walkthrough": "Run `report_timing -from state_reg_7/Q -to state_reg_3/D`. Walk the path: the sbox_mux -> sbox_lut segment has 85 ps of wire delay on n_mux_y, which is dominant. `get_nets -pattern n_mux_y` confirms high capacitance (0.028 pF). The MUX4X1 driver is too weak. Pick size_up_mux (best slack recovery) or buffer_insert (smaller PPA hit)."
  }
